oai_dc:dc.dc:title: The Spoils of Our October 'Victory'!
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Political cartoon interpreting what the artist believed was gained as a result of the Bay of Pigs Invasion and the Cuban Missile Crisis.

The Jack Knox Papers, 1932-1978, represent the work of a noted conservative political cartoonist who drew for the Nashville Banner newspaper. Mr. Knox retired in 1975 after 29 years with the Nashville Banner.
